Description: Titan VMOS — Antidetect Android Device Platform (Cuttlefish KVM)
 Production-grade KVM-based Android 14 virtualization platform running
 Google Cuttlefish VMs with 103+ anti-detect vectors, AI-driven device
 automation, profile forging, wallet provisioning, and Play Integrity
 defense via Magisk/TrickyStore/PlayIntegrityFork.
 .
 V13.0 Features:
  - Up to 8 concurrent Android 14 VMs (Cuttlefish KVM)
  - 28-phase anomaly patcher (103+ stealth vectors)
  - Pre-bundled Cuttlefish images + CVD host tools
  - Pre-bundled GApps APKs (GMS, Play Store, Chrome, YouTube, Wallet)
  - Genesis profile forge (contacts, SMS, call logs, cookies, gallery)
  - Wallet provisioning (Google Pay tap-and-pay token injection)
  - AI agent automation (Ollama LLM See→Think→Act loop)
  - Real-time screen streaming (ws-scrcpy H.264 + JPEG fallback)
  - Play Integrity defense (TrickyStore + PIF Zygisk modules)
  - Keybox lifecycle management (validate, rotate, revocation check)
  - FastAPI server with 18 routers (62+ endpoints)
  - Web console + optional Electron desktop UI
  - Device recovery watchdog (auto-restart stalled VMs)
  - NUMA-aware CPU pinning for anti-timing fingerprinting
